====Definitions====
{{head|zh|hanzi}}

# to [[dominate]]
#* {{zh-x|管 仲 相{xiàng} ^桓-公，霸 諸侯，一-匡 ^天下，民 到 于今 受 其 賜。|Guan Zhong helped Duke Huan [of Qi] to '''dominate''' the various princes, thus unifying and rectifying the realm. Until now the people are still receiving the gifts of his [endeavors].|ref=Lunyu}}
# {{lb|zh|historical}} [[overlord]], [[hegemon]]
#* {{zh-x|三-王 五霸，其 所 道 不過 爵-祿，而 功 相 萬 者，其 所 道 明 也。|The principle followed by the Three Kings and the '''{{w|Five Hegemons}}''' was no other than that of giving titles and emoluments, and the reason that people emulated each other in merit was because the principles which they followed were clear.|ref=Shangjunshu-D}}
# [[tyrant]]; [[despot]]; [[bully]]
#* {{zh-x|以-力 假-仁 者 霸，霸 必 有 大-國，以-德 行-仁 者 王，王 不 待 大。|He who uses force while feigning humaneness is a '''despot'''; '''despots''' certainly crave large states. He who uses virtues to practice humaneness is a sovereign; sovereigns need no large states.|ref=Mengzi}}
# [[hegemony]]; [[tyranny]]
#* {{zh-x|十五 年，春，復 會 焉，齊 始 霸 也。|In the 15th year, in spring, [the rulers] again met there. Qi exerted its '''hegemony''' for the first time.|ref=Zuozhuan}}
#* {{zh-x|釐{Xī}-王 三-年，^齊 ^桓-公 始 霸。|In King Xi's third year, Duke Huan of Qi exerted his '''hegemony''' for the first time.|ref=Shiji}}
# to [[occupy]]; to [[monopolize]]
#: {{zh-x|霸佔|to forcibly occupy, to seize}}
#: {{zh-x|霸機|to stage a sit-in after a plane has landed}}
#: {{zh-x|霸位{wai6-2}|to reserve a seat for someone who has not yet arrived|C}}
# {{lb|zh|Eastern Min}} [[powerful]]; [[awesome]]; [[impressive]]
#:  {{zh-x|伊 野 霸|s/he is '''awesome'''|MD|tr=ĭ iā-*bá}}

